<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1476,2043]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1548,1574]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Mandibular plates equal than clypeus. Proportions of antennomeres: 1&gt; 2 &lt;3&gt; 4 &lt;5 (Fig. 96). Posterior margins of bucculae reaching base of head. Labium median, attaining the metacoxae (Fig. 94). Proportions of labiomeres: 1 &lt;2&gt; 3&gt; 4. Each peritreme of ESES reaching about 1/3 of the distance to lateral margin of evaporatorium. Median furrow of the peritreme short, reaching less than half of peritreme. Evaporatorium on mesopleuron reaching more than half of the segment. Metathoracic spiracle wide. Hemelytra not surpassing the abdominal apex (
<figureCitation box="[160,243,1728,1755]" captionStart="FIGURES 55–59" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1825,1849]" captionTargetBox="[170,1414,291,1781]" captionTargetId="figure-67@10.[151,1436,273,1802]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 55–59. Hypatropis Bergroth, 1891. Holotype, habitus dorsal. 55: H. australis; 56: H. inermis; 57: H. rolstoni; 58: H. similis; 59: H. sternalis. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4897404" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4897404/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
). Connexivum exposed, anterior angles not concolour to dorsal color. Spiracles circular, spiracle of abdominal sternite 2 not covered by metathorax. Mesial area adjacent to spiracles with callosity.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1476,2043]" box="[199,525,1800,1827]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,382,1801,1827]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Measurements.</emphasis>
See 
<tableCitation box="[435,519,1800,1827]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="39.[151,239,491,517]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="TABLE 1. Morphometric parameters measured of complex Hypatropis species. Abbreviations: A1, length of antennomere 1; A2, length of antennomere 2; A3, length of antennomere 3; A4, length of antennomere 4; A5, length of antennomere 5; BW, body width; BL, body length; CL, length of clypeus; HL, head length; HLE, length of head at compound eye level; HW, head width; IOD, interocular distance; L1, length of labiomere 1; L2, length of labiomere 2; L3, length of labiomere 3; L4, length of labiomere 4; PL, pronotum length; PW, pronotum width; SL, scutellum length; SW, scutellum width." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF5B9395FFA3FFE1C2FCC4D1B1DCFDB1" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" tableUuid="DF5B9395FFA3FFE1C2FCC4D1B1DCFDB1">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1476,2043]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,378,1836,1863]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Posterolateral angles of pygophore quadrate. Genital cup occupying more than half of pygophore length. Extension of dorsal rim obsolete. Layers of ventral rim not separated by a carina; area between layers excavated. Inferior layer of ventral rim without process. 
<taxonomicName box="[777,863,1908,1934]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Phallaceae" genus="Phallus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Phallales" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[777,863,1908,1934]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Phallus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: Dorsal connectives shorter, reaching the middle of 
<emphasis box="[151,283,1944,1970]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">phallotheca</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[296,501,1945,1970]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Processus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="capitati">
<emphasis box="[296,501,1945,1970]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Processus capitati</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
longer, surpassing 
<emphasis box="[714,846,1944,1970]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">phallotheca</emphasis>
distal margin. Dorsal processes of 
<emphasis box="[1234,1366,1944,1970]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">phallotheca</emphasis>
wider at the base, shorter than posterodorsal projections (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Fernandes, J. A. M. &amp; Grazia, J." box="[765,1175,1980,2007]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" pagination="341 - 352" refId="ref22412" refString="Fernandes, J. A. M. &amp; Grazia, J. (1996) Revisao do genero Hypatropis Bergroth, 1891 (Heteroptera, Pentatomidae). Revista Brasileira de Entomologia, 40 (3 / 4), 341 - 352." type="journal article" year="1996">Fernandes &amp; Grazia, 1996: 348–350</bibRefCitation>
, figs 21, 26, 31).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
